rom ~100 to ~1000\\AA and the ejecta\nexpansion both counteract the decrease in bolometric luminosity from ~10^11 to\n~10^9 L_sun over that period. Based on the observed detection efficiency of our\nstudy we make predictions for the breakout detection rate of the GALEX Time\nDomain Survey.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Apr 2008 20:00:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 25 Apr 2008 18:10:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 3 Jul 2008 21:34:36 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 31 Jul 2008 14:29:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
